What you need to know:

Mr Wambua confirmed that the dam currently has 2.53 meters remaining before spillage.Water Resources Authority has also warned that parts of Lodwar town near Turkwel River risk being submerged.Mr Shurie said that lives could be lost if residents living downstream do not move to higher grounds.County Director of Disaster Management Vincent Palor said that a technical team has been formed to develop a contingency plan.